Review: I feel like Mean Girls was the last movie on earth that needed a remake, it’s perfectly early 2000s. Regardless of if we need it or not, it’s here, and I dunno it’s alright.
I’m not really the target audience for this movie so don’t listen to me, just go see it it’s really good

“Ever since I was a child, people said my family was cursed“It’s all one long match. We fight, take bumps, get back up and do it all over again. They say what doesn’t kill you makes you stronger, but why does each hit hurt more than the last? As much as it can take from you, the pain you experience can give just as much. It teaches us, inspires us, strengthens us. Don’t shake it off or try and…
Honestly I expected a little better. Santa Harbour carries this movie, but not super far. Could’ve been a lot shorter
Even more fun if you watch it with a toddler

Something about this movie just really gets me. I find myself very much drawn to these films that embrace the wonder of human connection (Before Sunrise, Dead Poets Society, etc). This movie is very simple but I think its lack of a desire to overstate itself is a part of its charm. This’ll probably be a yearly watch for me from now on, and just an all time favorite in general
Cailee Spaeny is incredible here. Sofia Coppola’s directing is so good. Not a spectacular movie but one that definitley feels important
I put this on for my dad and it was like putting on cocomelon for a toddler
